*.env

# Each engagement under engagements/ is its OWN standalone git repository
# (see .claude/skills/init-engagement/SKILL.md and operations/guides/02_MAINTENANCE.md).
# The harness repo must not track engagement contents — that would defeat the isolation
# the whole point of per-engagement repos is to provide (separate history, separate
# lifecycle, no risk of one client's data ending up in another's or the harness
# template's own git log). Exception: a short README explaining this stays tracked so
# anyone browsing the harness repo understands why the directory looks empty here.
engagements/*
!engagements/README.md

# --- Next.js dashboard (app/) build artifacts ---
# The dashboard lives in app/ as its own bun project with its own app/.gitignore.
# Anything Next generates at the HARNESS repo root is a stray from accidentally
# running `next` outside app/ — never track it here.
.next/
next-env.d.ts
/tsconfig.json
*.tsbuildinfo
node_modules/
*.log

# Git worktrees created under .claude/ are local scratch, never repo content.
.claude/worktrees/
.sensai/
